author: sascharodekamp
msg: FIX: Wrong use of toArray() method (https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OFBIZ-4425). A patch from Dimitri Unruh which replaces Array Casts with a propper call of the toArray method.
String[] temp = (String[]) foo.toArray(); <-- may cause class cast exception it is better to use: String[] temp = foo.toArray(new String[foo.size()])
